org.svvrl.goal.core.aut.opt

Class EfficientSimulation2

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.svvrl.goal.core.aut.opt.AbstractSimulation2
      • org.svvrl.goal.core.aut.opt.EfficientSimulation2
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Simulation2

    public class EfficientSimulation2
extends AbstractSimulation2
    This class provides an implementation of the procedure EfficientSimilarity in [Monika Rauch Henzinger, Thomas A. Henzinger, Peter W. Kopke: Computing Simulations on Finite and Infinite Graphs. FOCS 1995: 453-462] for computing simulation relations between two automata. Note that the alphabets of the input automata must be the same and non-empty.
    Author:
    Ming-Hsien Tsai

        public EfficientSimulation2(FSA aut1,
                            FSA aut2)
        Constructs this object to compute the simulation relation between two automata. The two automata are assumed to have the same label position, the same alphabet type, and the same acceptance condition. The fair simulation is considered.
        Parameters:

        aut2 - an automaton
